Table 1. Quantitative comparison of image dehazing methods trained on different datasets. For the compared methods, we use bold, and 
underline to mark the best and second best methods. For gUNet, we use bold or underline to indicate that the model is better than the best 
or second best of compared methods.

Table 2. Ablation study of network architectures and training strategies on different datasets. The results marked in green or red means 
there is an improvement or degradation compared to the baseline (gUNet-T). We train baseline five times and take the best and worst.
